The police yesterday arraigned Habeeb Azeez at an Ikorodu Magistratesâ€™ Court, Lagos, for allegedly stealing a copper wire valued at N55,000. Azeez, 19, whose address was not provided by the court, is facing a one-count charge bordering on stealing. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Sergeant John Iberedem alleged that the defendant committed the offence on May 14, at 23/24, Ayangburen Road, opposite Palace Club House, Ikorodu. He alleged that the defendant stole the property, belonging to Olusegun Kadejo. The prosecutor said the offence contravened Section 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Chief Magistrate F.A. Azeez admitted the defendant to N50, 000 bail with one surety in like sum. The case was adjourned till June 2.